# Live Site URL

**The live site URL is always `https://ail.mysalesforcedemo.com`.**

This is the canonical production URL for the AI Library. Use it anywhere a production URL is referenced.

## Required Usage

- In rules, docs, READMEs, summaries, deploy reports, and commit/PR descriptions: refer to production as `https://ail.mysalesforcedemo.com`.
- For browser testing, `curl`, `fetch`, or any HTTP tool targeting the deployed app: use `https://ail.mysalesforcedemo.com` (or paths under it).
- When reporting a successful deploy back to the user, cite `https://ail.mysalesforcedemo.com` — not the `*.herokuapp.com` URL.
- In config values (`CORS_ORIGIN`, `APP_BASE_URL`, `GOOGLE_CALLBACK_URL` host, etc.): use `https://ail.mysalesforcedemo.com`.

## Forbidden

Do NOT present any of the following as the live site URL:

- `https://aosfail-2a55fb282d59.herokuapp.com/` or any other `*.herokuapp.com` host
- `https://sfpl.mysalesforcedemo.com` (legacy)
- `http://localhost:*`, `http://127.0.0.1:*`, or any dev host

The `*.herokuapp.com` host is the Heroku dyno origin behind the CDN/DNS; reference it only when explicitly discussing the Heroku dyno itself (logs, release names). Never as "the live site."

## Example

- Good: "Deployed — live at https://ail.mysalesforcedemo.com."
- Bad: "Deployed — live at https://aosfail-2a55fb282d59.herokuapp.com/."
